text: Behold the cosmic stare-down: Jupiter, the king of planets, caught in a mesmerizing Hubble snapshot where its colossal Great Red Spot‚Äîthat swirling vortex of fury twice Earth's diameter, with winds howling at 400 mph‚Äîgets an eerie upgrade. Right smack in the center drifts the inky shadow of Ganymede, Jupiter's beefiest moon (bigger than Mercury and the only one with its own magnetic field), turning the crimson storm into a gigantic, unblinking eye peering through the void straight at us! Captured on April 21, 2014, during Hubble's watchful eye on the shrinking GRS, this serendipitous transit gives the gas giant a Cyclops vibe that's equal parts spooky and sublime.This isn't just a pretty picture‚Äîit's a reminder of Jupiter's dynamic dance with its 95+ moons. Ganymede orbits every 7 days, but alignments like this, where its shadow perfectly pupils the Spot, are rare treats for astronomers. Fast-forward to 2025, and we've had fresh thrills: Just days ago on November 5, skywatchers could spot double shadows from Io and Europa crossing Jupiter's clouds (grab a telescope next time!), echoing these Hubble gems.

text:
The CFIA‚Äôs Ostrich Cull ‚Äî A Shameful Day for Canada!!

What happened in Edgewood, British Columbia is nothing short of disgusting.

The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) authorized the killing of innocent, healthy ostriches without transparency, without proper testing, and without giving those animals or their owners a fair chance.

They didn‚Äôt even allow independent testing before ordering the cull. Why? What are they hiding?

This isn‚Äôt science.
This isn‚Äôt biosecurity.
This is bureaucratic cruelty.

The way the CFIA handled this, ‚Äîarriving like enforcers, silencing questions, and refusing to provide proof, is an absolute disgrace to Canadian values.
Where was the due process? Where was the evidence? Where was the compassion?

Canadians have every right to be furious.
And we are.

We‚Äôve seen overreach before ‚Äî but this one hit differently. These were living creatures, cared for by people who loved them and trusted the system to be fair. Instead, that trust was shattered.

And honestly, it‚Äôs hard not to see the parallel.
We watched the same kind of fear and control tactics during COVID ‚Äî where people were treated like threats instead of human beings, where ‚Äúpositive‚Äù tests became sentences, and ‚Äúfalse positives‚Äù were brushed aside.
The pattern is the same: no transparency, no accountability, and no respect for the people.
Let‚Äôs be clear ‚Äî the people are supposed to be the boss of the government, not the other way around.
Public servants are meant to serve, not rule.

This entire event must be investigated and audited.
The CFIA must be held accountable for its actions.
And if those responsible acted without integrity, they must be removed from their positions ‚Äî period.

Where were the police? The ones sworn to serve and protect? When the people needed them most, too many stood silent. Some enforced what they knew was wrong; others just looked away. Every officer, every official, every bystander who chose comfort over courage bears a share of this. 

God have mercy on their souls because history won‚Äôt. 

This is not about one farm anymore.
It‚Äôs about truth, transparency, and trust in the very institutions meant to serve and protect Canadians ‚Äî not silence them.

This can never be allowed to happen again!

text:
A new wave of controversy surrounds non-browning apples and potatoes. A tiny double-stranded RNA (dsRNA) silences the browning gene, sparking debate about safety and transparency.

In honeybees, one dsRNA meal shifted expression of over 1,400 genes‚Äîabout 10% of the genome‚Äîwithin weeks. Similar shifts have been seen in mice when dsRNA is included in their diet. The big question: could the RNA fragments we eat alter our own genetic activity?

Regulators are portrayed as unprepared to assess long-term RNA effects from food, and critics argue peer-reviewed studies aren‚Äôt translating into clear safeguards. The USDA‚Äôs position is seen by some as insufficient for consumer reassurance.

This pits convenience and shelf-life against biological uncertainty. Should there be stricter vetting, more transparent data, or consumer opt-outs as dsRNA crops become more common?

text:
A Call for Transparency from XENEA

The Xenea team needs to communicate more clearly with its community by providing update on estimated timelines, and detailed explanations for any delays related to the TGE.

We understand that delay does not mean failure in fact, in the crypto space, it often means that a team is taking time to build something solid and sustainable, rather than rushing out an unstable project.

For example, Arbitrum and zkSync both experienced extended testnet phases and multiple postponements before finally launching their mainnets. Today, they stand among the most respected Layer-2 scaling solutions in the entire Ethereum ecosystem.

That said, transparency remains a vital part of community trust. So, consistent communication restores confidence and strengthens the bond between a project and its users.

Right now, many Xenea testnet participants are beginning to lose hope, not because they have lost faith in Xenea‚Äôs vision, but because they feel they're left in dark, with no clear communication to assure them that the team is still actively building.

In the evolving Web3 landscape, where community trust is the backbone of every successful project, silence can easily breed uncertainty.

So, we're calling on Xenea  be more transparent especially on TGE and other milestones, inorder to restore confidence and trust of its growing community.

Because a transparent project is a trusted project, and a trusted project always wins in the long run.

@uharatokuro @Xenea_io @yuma_xenea

text:
While you wait weeks to see a GP, NHS doctors in England are being forced into unemployment; blocked by Government caps that stop them from furthering their training to become specialist Consultants/GPs.

This year, there were around 30,000 doctors applying for 10,000 speciality training places. That means thousands of capable doctors ready to serve the public and the NHS are being turned away.

Every rejected doctor is a lost opportunity to cut waiting lists, staff wards safely and bring the NHS back from crisis.

And @wesstreeting‚Äôs response? Just 2,000 extra speciality training places over 3 years.

That will not fix the doctor unemployment crisis in England. It will continue to leave patients waiting months for care and will push doctors out of the NHS altogether.

This is one of the reasons why NHS resident doctors are going back out on strike.

Doctors want to work. Patients want care. It‚Äôs the Government that‚Äôs standing in the way.

#EndTrainingCrisis

Rayls is building a unified financial network where banks, fintechs, and innovators can fully transact, settle, and build on-chain.
@RaylsLabs combines privacy and compliance without sacrificing transparency. It enables sub-millisecond settlements, makes programmable trust a standard, allows institutions to run private yet auditable operations, and automates regulated credit and debt issuance.

Through on-chain FX and stablecoin corridors, it connects global markets while merging private and public networks into one interoperable system.
In short, Rayls is creating the infrastructure for a new era where one hundred trillion dollars in institutional liquidity will flow through a single programmable network.

Rayls is not just a bridge, it is the backbone of unified finance.

text:
BAM, KIKO ADVANCE TRANSPARENCY AND ACCOUNTABILITY BILLS TO COMBAT CORRUPTION

Senators Bam Aquino and Kiko Pangilinan on Wednesday, November 12, advanced key legislation aimed at ensuring that government funds and programs truly benefit Filipinos.

Senate Bill No. 1506, or the proposed Citizen Access and Disclosure of Expenditures for National Accountability (CADENA) Act, sponsored and authored by Aquino, seeks to curb the misuse of public funds and enhance citizen participation in the national budget process through a digital budget portal that promotes full disclosure and transparency.

Aquino, chair of the Senate Committee on Science and Technology, said the measure institutionalizes a "technological solution" to corruption, with provisions mandating the publication of all budget-related documents and penalties for agencies that fail to comply.

"Sinisigurado ng CADENA Act na mababantayan ng taumbayan ang pinaghirapan nilang buwis, at malalaman ng sambayanang Pilipino kung paano ginagastos ang kaban ng bayan," he said. "Kaya sigurado ako na ang tanging matatakot lang sa CADENA, ay ang mga kurakot na mayroong tinatago."

Meanwhile, the Senate also took up Senate Bill No. 1512, or the proposed Independent People's Commission (IPC) Act, sponsored and co-authored by Pangilinan. The measure seeks to establish a non-partisan, fact-finding body empowered to investigate, document, and recommend actions on anomalies in government infrastructure projects.

Pangilinan, chair of the Senate Committee on Justice and Human Rights, described the IPC as the "people's watchdog" against massive corruption.

"Unprecedented ang kurakot. Unprecedented ang bunga ng krimen. Kailangan unprecedented din ang pag papanagot," he said.

The IPC would have the authority to issue subpoenas, freeze assets, blacklist erring contractors, grant witness immunity, and deputize law enforcement agencies to support investigations. Pangilinan said its creation is a "commitment they must fulfill for every Filipino who lost their loved ones, their homes, and their livelihoods to the massive flooding caused by ghost, substandard, and failed infrastructure projects."

text:
One of the key features of the blockchain is the transparency it brings.

I'm a Fundamental Analyst and Trader, so i may likely speak from that angle.

Saying this off heart so it may not be orderly and how you would want it arranged, but let's delve inüëá

As a newbie, trust what the blockchain says and not what people say.
Trust the data, the metrics, and the liquidity flow.
Be accountable for all outcomes of every decision you take, don't blame others, and also do not over trust words

Not every narrative should be front-ran
Sometimes, the majority of the narratives you want to front run may never gain that visibility or hype anytime soon.
Learn to agree that some meta/ narratives are one-offs.

If you are a trader, try to figure out structures and patterns that work and follow them judiciously.
It could be a certain agency/ incubator you studied that always launches great projects, Daos that affiliates itself with quality projects, a Launchpad, a certain cabal/ set of KOLs that talk about AA+ projects etc.

You should also understand that patience is very required to hit that big win.

The majority of the wins and big runner i have had are from the projects i waited long enough before they even launched. I just simply had to research and keep vetting them prior to their launch.

Understand the macro effect and picture of the markets before taking major moves.
Even the projects you will trade take their time to study the markets to know when to launch, what chain to launch, narratives to launch, not to talk of you as a newbie that has barely interacted onchain.
Take time to truly learn.

Do not under look this rule "Be Fearful when others are greedy, and be greedy when others are fearful."

Most persons will always want to  create hopium for you to follow, but you must truly look at the bigger picture of the market.

What are the recent news happening globally?

Are there any ongoing wars or recent catastrophes that could affect the global economy?

What's the greed and fear index of the market?
People could still be bullposting at levels where it's extremely greedy.
Be wise, don't fall for it

"Be Fearful when others are greedy, and Greedy when others are Fearful" is one quote that would save you a lot in the crypto/web3 space.

On narratives,
Read Research Papers
Check out for recent investments of the top VCs and foundations.
You may get a clue into the next big narrative or sector of money inflow.

Tools are your first networks to gain access into the numerous database and information flow in web3, learn how to use them.

Build direct/ indirect networks across people who inspire you. It could be through stalking them, daily conversations or being part of rooms they are also. Fight your way to get into these rooms, and when you do, make sure to never be the weaklink so you don't fallout of such networks.
Attend events if you must to build your social capital and make yourself useful to those you admire and want to gain knowledge from no matter how small.

Understand protocols for what they are and not just barely for the hype. In the ve 3,3 and solidly season, a lot of persons who thoroughly learnt about this mechanism made way more money from the yields and bribes compared to those who traded it solely.

During the Virtuals season, people who took their time to understand the long term vision, struture and plans for the ecosystem have made way much money off their genesis launches, tokens launched under the ecosystem than solely trading the token.

The attention-mindshare simulation game is also something you must learn. Always try to look beyond short term rewards and failures from a hyped project when there are numerous ways to best and play the game.
During the yapyo szn, we had all attention on arbitrum since they claimed to back it, the ARB token did over 40% with other Arbitrum based tokens running 2,3 to 5X like GRAIL, BOOP etc.

Recently, everyone on the TL was talking about Momentum Finance, especially after the prelaunch metrics (500m TVL)  and data they had which was mindblowing. Al attention was on the sui ecosystem and with that attention , the likes of LOFI quietly moved 3x, and HIPPO did over 4x.

what is common in both scenarios? over expectation from the majority on rewards to gain from both Yapyo and MMT.
MMT Airdroppers complained after launch, even when they had the chance to buy low on launch and ride it to over 2 billion mcap post-launch; Yapyo had a bad launch from team, but top players in the game study these pattern and mindshare hack and max it out by positioning for the gains to come from participating in the ecosystem itself.

Avoid playing the beta game, lest you become a beta.
Trade A is the main play and looks to gain the most support, why go for Trade B or C which could be one-offs and you may fail to take profits.

The phrase 'Ape now, Research Later' may only work if you are part of a good circle that really have good information and share more winning trades. Other than that, research always, it's better to ape a play at 2m mcap when you have gained strong conviction and sell at 50m mcap, than to see it early at 100k mcap and sell at 500k mcap because you lacked foresight to  develop the conviction and see the strength of that trade.

There are always going to be alpha, so never be sad when you miss one.
Infact, the beauty of the web3 space is in fact, the numerous alphas and opportunities it presents timely.
All you have to do is always be liquid and have capital.

For this same reasons, you must always take profits no matter what, and learn to cut losses when conviction starts fading.
It's best to have liquidity for the next alpha that could play out fine, than to be stuck on a trade that could send you to depression if you lose your money on it.
Also, for this same reason, never invest more than you can lose.

However, nobody really wants to lose more than they win, so you must learn the art of research and question everything.

As a content creator, be good with fundamental analysis and research, you want to write on leading trends, topics and feed the ego of the top chads in the space.

One way to break into the circle of the big guys is to write on some of the things they have convictions on and tag them to it.
Feed their ego , they would want to relate with you

Document publicly, learn from as much persons and groups you can, do not care what people would say and keep showing up daily.

"Consistency is no joke here", words from a wise one... but make sure not to be consistent with the wrong approach , systems, structures and patterns.
Have a daily checklist and to-do-list and be accountable and responsible to it.

You are the CEO of your life, connect with people who motivate and inspire you to be better, leave circles that drain you and are parasitic, know when to leave a particular strategy when it's not working.

Be Flexible, know when to relearn, know when to rinse and repeat, and know when to rinse and not repeat a strategy.
